returns._0: the account id of the smart account the accountId should be structured like so: "vendorname.accountname.semver"
bytes32 Hash of the domain separator.

execute(bytes32,bytes).details: this function is only callable by the entry point or the account itself

params.mode: The encoded execution mode of the transaction. See solady's LibERC7579.sol for details

executeFromExecutor(bytes32,bytes).details: this function is only callable by an installed executor module

params.mode: The encoded execution mode of the transaction. See solady's LibERC7579.sol for details

returns._0: Struct containing handler address and call type metadata.

initializeAccount(address[],bytes[]).details: All passed in modules have to be unique, and of exactly one module type.

params.data: Array of initialization data corresponding to each module
params.modules: Array of module addresses to be installed in the account

installModule(uint256,address,bytes).details: installs a Module of a certain type on the smart accountImplement Authorization control of your choosing

params.initData: arbitrary data that may be required on the module during `onInstall` initialization.
params.moduleTypeId: the module type ID according the ERC-7579 spec

params.additionalContext: additional context data that the smart account may interpret to                          identify conditions under which the module is installed.                          usually this is not necessary, but for some special hooks that                          are stored in mappings, this param might be needed
params.moduleTypeId: the module type ID according the ERC-7579 spec Note: keep in mind that some contracts can be multiple module types at the same time. It thus may be necessary to query multiple module types

isValidSignature(bytes32,bytes).details: ERC-1271 isValidSignature This function is intended to be used to validate a smart account signature and may forward the call to a validator module

params.hash: The hash of the data that is signed

params.attesters: List of attesters to trust immediately.
params.threshold: Minimum number of trusted attesters required by the registry.

params.moduleTypeId: the module type ID according the ERC-7579 spec

uninstallModule(uint256,address,bytes).details: uninstalls a Module of a certain type on the smart accountImplement Authorization control of your choosing

params.deInitData: arbitrary data that may be required on the module during `onUninstall` de-initialization.
params.moduleTypeId: the module type ID according the ERC-7579 spec

params.deInitData: ABI-encoded data forwarded to the uninstall routine when possible.
params.module: Address of the module to unlink.
params.moduleTypeId: Type identifier of the module being removed.

validateUserOp((address,uint256,bytes,by.details: ERC-4337 validateUserOp according to ERC-4337 v0.7         This function is intended to be called by ERC-4337 EntryPoint.sol this validation function should decode / sload the validator module to validate the userOp and call it.

domainSeparator().notice: Expose the current EIP-712 domain separator used for signatures.

getActiveFallbackHandler(bytes4).notice: Retrieve the fallback handler registered for a given selector.

initializeAccount(address[],bytes[]).notice: Initializes the account. Function might be called directly, or by a Factory.

isModuleInstalled(uint256,address,bytes).notice: Function to check if the account has a certain module installed

setRegistry(address,address[],uint8).notice: Configure the ERC-7484 registry used to attest modules for the account.

supportsExecutionMode(bytes32).notice: Function to check if the account supports a certain CallType or ExecType (see solady's LibERC7579.sol)

supportsModule(uint256).notice: Function to check if the account supports installation of a certain module type Id

unlinkModule(uint256,address,bytes).notice: Uninstall a module while allowing its cleanup to revert without bubbling up.
